Why a bridge function instead of changing one of the types:
  - ruff_spo_triplet::Triple and lance_graph_contract::Triple are
    field-for-field IDENTICAL (s,p,o,f,c) and both are upstream-neutral
    crates whose definitions should not couple to a downstream project.
  - A 5-line per-field clone in this crate is the seam: downstream pays
    for the bridge, upstream stays clean.

The workspace.exclude fix:
  - Vendor mirrors have their OWN standalone workspace roots (added in
    codex PR #6 P1 and Sprint C7). The ruff vendor's crates use
    `workspace = true` deps that resolve against the vendor workspace.
  - Without `exclude`, nexgen's `cargo` walks into the vendor dir and
    tries to inherit those `workspace = true` references from nexgen's
    workspace.dependencies, which doesn't define them.
  - lance-graph-contract didn't hit this earlier (Sprint C7) because its
    Cargo.toml uses NO workspace inheritance. The ruff crates do.
  - exclude = [vendor/...] tells cargo to leave both vendor trees to
    their own workspace roots; path-deps into the vendor still work.

